```
    <h1>Our Ethics</h1>

    <div class="intro">
        Every photograph tells a story. We make sure it's told with respect.
    </div>

    <div class="section">
        <h2>What We Promise</h2>
        <p>Every image on Scatto comes from photographers who understand that authentic storytelling requires ethical practices. We don't just curate beautiful photos—we curate responsible ones.</p>

        <p><strong style="color: var(--primary);">All photography is created with appropriate consent, community respect, and human dignity at the center.</strong></p>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
        <h2>Our Standards</h2>
        <p>We work with photographers who commit to:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Obtaining proper consent from individuals and communities</li>
            <li>Building genuine relationships, not extractive practices</li>
            <li>Representing people with dignity and avoiding harmful stereotypes</li>
            <li>Being transparent about how images will be used</li>
            <li>Respecting cultural contexts and local customs</li>
            <li>Never photographing identifiable minors without guardian consent</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
        <h2>Community First</h2>
        <p>The communities in our photographs aren't just subjects—they're partners in storytelling. We maintain systems for:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Community feedback and concerns</li>
            <li>Image removal requests</li>
            <li>Ongoing photographer accountability</li>
            <li>Cultural sensitivity review</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
        <h2>Real-World Ethics</h2>
        <p>We understand that ethical photography looks different in different contexts. A community meeting requires different consent than a public rally. Emergency documentation has different constraints than planned portraits.</p>

        <p>Our approach is principled but practical—always prioritizing human dignity while recognizing the realities of documentary work.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
        <h2>Why This Matters</h2>
        <p>Impact organizations deserve imagery that reflects their values. Communities deserve representation that honors their stories. Photographers deserve to work within ethical frameworks that support meaningful storytelling.</p>

        <p>When you use Scatto, you're not just getting better photos—you're supporting better practices.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="contact">
        <h2>Questions or Concerns?</h2>
        <p>We're committed to transparency and continuous improvement.</p>
        <p>Reach us at: <a href="<mailto:ethics@scatto.photos>">ethics@scatto.photos</a></p>
    </div>
</div>

